content: Many of us have that one teacher who is a life changer. The instructor that weaves critical life lessons into the traditional subject matter. For me that teacher is Canton High School Mathematics Legend Martin Badoian. I can recall making the decision to struggle through his class vs. enrolling in a lower level course. Best C+ I ever got. On this Teacher Appreciation Day I send a heartfelt thank you to Mr. B for the years of inspiration. I tell Emily and Ethan about you all the time. Congratulations on your 6+ decades of teaching brilliance.
name: Lee Goldberg
title: PROFILES: For six decades, Badoian has helped students just do the math

Early call (hope) for the holiday weekend:

Friday: Rain exits early. Clouds and sunny breaks with a pm shower. Highs in the low to mid 70s. 

Saturday : Partly sunny. Highs in the upper 70s.

Sunday (most unsettled day) : Sun then clouds. Chance for showers and t-storms. Highs in the low to 70s.

Memorial Day: Partly Sunny with a spot shower or t-storm. Warmer. High around 80.

content:
Updated Holiday Weekend Weather Outlook

Biggest adjustment: Sunday trending drier. Approaching area of low pressure looks slower. Late Sunday night into early Monday morning  looking like the wettest part of the weekend.

Friday: Morning rain. Clouds and late day sunny breaks (better chance south) with a leftover shower. Highs in the low 70s. 

Saturday: Partly sunny. Highs in the upper 70s.

Sunday: Sun and clouds. Spot afternoon shower or t-storm. Highs in the mid to upper 70s.

Memorial Day: Early showers/t-storm then clouds break for some sun. Highs in the mid 70s.

content:
Not so warm, but not too wet either this Memorial Day Weekend. Most of Saturday and Sunday will be dry. Best chance for rain is Sunday night into Monday morning. Here are the details:

Saturday: Sunny start then clouds increase. An afternoon shower, mainly west and south. High: 72.

Sunday: Clouds and sun. A touch cooler due to an onshore breeze. High: 68.

Monday: A damp start then clouds may break for a little sun. Still a shower or two around during the afternoon. High: 72.
